     <script language="javascript" type="text/javascript">
      var navSearch = new Object();
     navSearch.focused = false;
     var divHeader;
     var timeoutHnd1;
     var alreadyrunflag = false //flag to indicate document "ready" has already been run
     var menuVisible = false;
 
     // A "document ready" method for FF and IE.  Other browsers will be relegated to window.onload
     if (document.addEventListener)
         addListener(document, "DOMContentLoaded", function () { alreadyrunflag = true; domReady(); }, false);
     else if (document.all && !window.opera) {
         document.write('<script type="text/javascript" id="contentloadtag" defer="defer" src="javascript:void(0)"><\/script>')
         var contentloadtag = document.getElementById("contentloadtag")
         contentloadtag.onreadystatechange = function () {
             if (this.readyState == "complete") {
                 alreadyrunflag = true;
                 domReady();
             }
         }
     }
 
     addListener(window, 'load', function () { setTimeout("if (!alreadyrunflag) { domReady(); }", 0) }, true);
 
     function searchvalueChanged(obj) {
         if (navSearch.focused) {
             if (obj.value.indexOf("Search") != -1) {
                 obj.value = "";
             }
         }
         else {
             if (obj.value == "") {
                 obj.value = "Search";
             }
         }
     }
 
     // Maintain focus/blur of navSearch when the menu is displayed so that the underlying
     // edit cursor is not displayed
     function domReady() {
         if (document.getElementsByClassName == undefined) {
             document.getElementsByClassName = function (className) {
                 var hasClassName = new RegExp("(?:^|\\s)" + className + "(?:$|\\s)");
                 var allElements = document.getElementsByTagName("*");
                 var results = [];
                 var element;
                 for (var i = 0; (element = allElements[i]) != null; i++) {
                     var elementClass = element.className;
                     if (elementClass && elementClass.indexOf(className) != -1 && hasClassName.test(elementClass))
                         results.push(element);
                 }
                 return results;
             }
         }
 
         navSearch = document.getElementsByClassName('sf_searchText')[0];
         divHeader = document.getElementById('ctl00_Corporate_Navigation_970_ctl00_divHeaderImage');
         navSearch.focused = false;
         addListener(navSearch, 'blur', function (maintainFocus) { navSearch.focused = false; searchvalueChanged(navSearch); }, true);
         addListener(navSearch, 'focus', function () { navSearch.focused = true; searchvalueChanged(navSearch); }, true);
         addListener(divHeader, 'click', function () { window.location = '/main/Home.aspx'; }, false);
         // Example of adding a DOM element with just JavaScript
         //        var inp = document.createElement('input');
         //        inp.id = 'hiddenInput';
         //        inp.setAttribute('type', 'text');
         //        inp.style.left = '-3300px';
         //        document.body.appendChild(inp);
     }
 
     // Cross-browser implementation of element.addEventListener()
     // so that jQuery isn't needed.
     function addListener(element, type, expression, bubbling) {
         if (typeof (expression) != 'function') return false;
         bubbling = bubbling || false;
         if (element.addEventListener) { // Standard
             element.addEventListener(type, expression, bubbling);
             return true;
         }
         else if (element.attachEvent) { // IE
             element.attachEvent('on' + type, expression);
             return true;
         }
         return false;
     }
 
     // Cross-browser implementation of element.removeEventListener()
     // so that jQuery isn't needed.
     function removeListener(element, type, expression, bubbling) {
         if (typeof (expression) != 'function') return false;
         bubbling = bubbling || false;
         if (element.removeEventListener) {
             element.removeEventListener(type, expression, bubbling);
             return true;
         } else if (element.detachEvent) {
             element.detachEvent('on' + type, expression);
             return true;
         }
         return false;
     }
 
     // Cross-browser method to trigger an event on an element
     function triggerEvent(element, type) {
         if (typeof (element) != 'object') return;
         var e;
         if (document.dispatchEvent) { // W3C
             var htmlEvents = ['abort', 'blur', 'change', 'error', 'focus', 'load', 'reset', 'resize', 'scroll', 'select', 'submit', 'unload'];
             var uiEvents = ['DOMActivate', 'DOMFocusIn', 'DOMFocusOut', 'keydown', 'keypress', 'keyup'];
             var mouseEvents = ['click', 'mousedown', 'mousemove', 'mouseout', 'mouseover', 'mouseup'];
 
             var module;
             // Technically, all events could be triggered as HTMLEvents
             if (htmlEvents.indexOf(type) > -1)
                 module = 'HTMLEvents';
             if (uiEvents.indexOf(type) > -1)
                 module = 'UIEvents';
             if (mouseEvents.indexOf(type) > -1)
                 module = 'MouseEvents';
 
             e = document.createEvent(module);
             switch (module) {
                 case 'HTMLEvents':
                     {
                         e.initEvent(type, true, true);
                         break;
                     }
                 case 'UIEvents':
                     {
                         e.initUIEvent(type, true, true, window, 1);
                         e.keyCode = 13;
                         break;
                     }
                 case 'MouseEvents':
                     {
                         e.initMouseEvent(type, true, true, window, 1, 1, 1, 1, 1, false, false, true, false, 0, null);
                         break;
                     }
             }
 
             return !element.dispatchEvent(e);
         }
         else if (element.fireEvent) { // IE
             e = document.createEventObject();
             return element.fireEvent("on" + type, e);
         }
     }
 
     // Simple method to get all elements that have a particular class name.
     // tag name can be passed in to pre-filter the search
     function getElementsByClassName(oElm, strTagName, strClassName) {
         var arrElements = (strTagName == "*" && document.all) ? document.all : oElm.getElementsByTagName(strTagName);
         var arrReturnElements = new Array();
         strClassName = strClassName.replace(/\-/g, "\\-");
         var oRegExp = new RegExp("(^|\\s)" + strClassName + "(\\s|$)");
         var oElement;
         for (var i = 0; i < arrElements.length; i++) {
             oElement = arrElements[i];
             if (oRegExp.test(oElement.getAttribute("class"))) {
                 arrReturnElements.push(oElement);
             }
         }
         return (arrReturnElements)
     }
 
     // On mouseover, blur navSearch so that the caret is not visible through the radmenu
     function menuMouseOver(menu, args) {
         menuVisible = true;

             clearTimeout(timeoutHnd1);

             if (navSearch.focused) {
                 navSearch.blur();
             }
         }, 200);
     }
 
     // On mouseout, return focus to the navSearch if it had it to begin with
     function menuMouseOut(menu, args) {

     }

                 <p>
                  <strong>
                   <br/>
                   Anywhere Anytime Order Entry
                  </strong>
                 </p>
                 <p>
                  Created for fast and convenient online order entry, this Internet-based service requires no additional software and offers order confirmation, tracking, product usage reports, and pricing information.
                 </p>
                 <p>
                  • Order guides based on preference
                  <br/>
                  • Item searches and descriptions
                  <br/>
                  • Pricing per serving and case
                  <br/>
                  • Items in stock at FSA
                  <br/>
                  • Helpful usage reporting
                 </p>
                 <p>

                  </strong>
                 </p>
                 <p>
                  <strong>
                  </strong>

                  <br/>
                  • Import orders from external files and check online before sending
                  <br/>
                  • Create orders from order guides
                  <br/>
                  • View invoice information
                  <br/>
                  • Generate reports by product, category, brand, or manufacturer
                  <br/>
                  • Track inventory status
                 </p>
                 <p>

                <div class="contentbody" id="ctl00_Left_Nav_Content_164_ctl00_lvFlyouts_ctrl11_divDescription">

                 <br/>
                 <br/>
                 “I’ve been using kitchen software for about 10 years and Star Solutions is definitely the best.”
                 <br/>
                 <br/>
                 – Bernie Eckroth, GM of Doublewood Inn in Bismark, North Dakota
                 <br/>
                 <br/>
                 “It saves me money, time, and energy.”  – Matt Neltner, Chef at Deschutes Brewery, Bend Oregon
                 <br/>
                 <br/>
                 “I’m not a real computer guy, but it’s an easy to use program.”  – Drew Leger, Chef at The Reef in Boise, Idaho
                 <br/>
                 <br/>
                 FREE to qualified customers. Retail value approximately $3,000. Contact us today for a demonstration.
                 <br/>
                 <br/>
                 <br/>
                 ** Embedded in Star Solutions Operator is software for a handheld device used to scan barcodes to generate an order or count inventory items. (Hardware must be purchased, contact Sales Associate for details.)

                  Customer Ordering Interactive Network (COIN) interfaces easily with your own ordering systems software so you can place orders with FSA.
